parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver's side seatbelt buckle can prevent the seatbelt from properly restraining the driver in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The driver's side seatbelt buckle will not latch
the buckle becomes unbuckled while driving
the buckle is intermittent and may catch occasionally
the insert of the buckle is completely gone.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of the brake lines can cause brake fluid leaks, leading to a loss of brake pressure, which can result in increased stopping distances and accidents.
symptoms: Brake pedal travels to the floor
brake fluid leaks from the brake lines
rust or corrosion visible on the brake lines.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the brake pads can cause a loss of braking performance, leading to increased stopping distances and accidents.
symptoms: Grinding or screeching noise when applying the brakes
brake pads wear down excessively
brake pads fail to stop the vehicle effectively.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inadequate brake performance can cause a loss of control or increased stopping distances, leading to accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle takes longer to stop than expected
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brakes are unable to stop the vehicle on steep inclines.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden loud banging noise
tire blowout
loss of air pressure
vibration or shaking of the vehicle
tread separation
flat tire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Poor-quality tires can lead to premature wear, uneven wear, and increased risk of tire failure, which can cause accidents and affect vehicle safety.
symptoms: Excessive vibration or shaking of the vehicle
uneven tire wear
tire noise
difficulty maintaining vehicle speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Uncommanded full throttle acceleration can cause the vehicle to suddenly and unexpectedly accelerate, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without input from the driver
the throttle sticks or becomes stuck
the vehicle surges forward unexpectedly
the driver experiences a loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the paint on the vehicle's body can lead to rust and corrosion, compromising the structural integrity of the vehicle and potentially causing safety issues.
symptoms: Cracks in the paint
flaking or peeling of the paint
exposed metal or rust spots on the vehicle's body.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Power Seat Switch Overheating and Fire Hazard
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The overheating of the power seat switch can cause a fire, potentially leading to injuries or fatalities, as well as damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Smoke or burning smell from the front door area
visible flames or sparks from the power seat switch
overheating or melting of the switch or surrounding components.
